# Node.js Version Governance

PrintHub uses one authoritative Node.js version. Contributors, Cursor agents, local development, and CI must all use the same version.

## Source of truth

**`.nvmrc`** is the canonical version. All other references derive from it:

| File | Must match `.nvmrc` |
|---|---|
| `package.json` → `engines.node` | Exact semver (e.g. `22.23.0`) |
| `.github/workflows/ci.yml` | `node-version-file: .nvmrc` — never hardcode a version |
| `README.md`, `docs/delivery/local-dev-setup.md`, `docs/delivery/deployment-runbook.md` | Document the pinned version |

Do not add a second source of truth (no duplicate `node-version:` in CI, no conflicting docs).

## GitHub Actions runtime vs application runtime

CI uses two separate Node contexts:

| Context | Source | Current |
|---|---|---|
| **Application Node** (build, test, E2E) | `.nvmrc` via `setup-node` `node-version-file` | Pinned semver (e.g. `22.23.0`) |
| **Action JavaScript runtime** (checkout, setup-node) | Action major version | Node 24 (`actions/checkout@v7`, `actions/setup-node@v6`) |

Do not conflate them. Upgrading action majors for Node 24 compatibility does **not** change the application Node version.

Minimum action majors are enforced in `tests/ci/workflow.test.ts`. When GitHub deprecates an action runtime, bump action majors and update that test file in the same change set.

## Local development

```bash
nvm install    # reads .nvmrc
nvm use
node --version # must match .nvmrc
```

## Upgrading Node.js

Any Node upgrade must update **all** of the following in the same change set:

1. `.nvmrc`
2. `package.json` → `engines.node`
3. `.github/workflows/ci.yml` (only if setup changes — version must still come from `.nvmrc`)
4. Documentation (`README.md`, `docs/delivery/local-dev-setup.md`, `docs/delivery/deployment-runbook.md`)
5. `@types/node` if the major line changes (stay on the same major as runtime)

After changing versions: run `npm install`, `npm run typecheck`, and `npm run test`.
